      <hedline>
        <hl1>Climate and Economy</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Lynn Kee letter says that, contrary to Pres Bush's opinion, Kyoto Protocol on global warming would help US economy by creating new technologies and new jobs (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Global Warming Follies'' (editorial, June 8):</p>
        <p>The main reason President Bush rejects the Kyoto Protocol is based on faulty reasoning; he believes that it would hurt the American economy. In fact, the opposite is true.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Global Warming Follies'' (editorial, June 8):</p>
        <p>The main reason President Bush rejects the Kyoto Protocol is based on faulty reasoning; he believes that it would hurt the American economy. In fact, the opposite is true.</p>
        <p>What is bad for Exxon is not necessarily bad for the United States economy. Ratifying Kyoto would spur new technologies and create millions of new jobs. This is just what our economy needs.</p>
        <p>LYNN KEE  Austin, Tex., June 8, 2002</p>
      </block>
